Three leading governorship candidates in Ekiti State, including the wife of Ekiti State Governor, Erelu Bisi Fayemi have endorsed the Vote-Not-Fight, Election No-Be-War Campaign being championed in the SouthWest by a non Governmental organisation, The New Generation Girls and Women Development Initiative (NIGAWD). The Vote Not Fight Campaign (VNF), which is being supported by USAID, UKAID and NDI is an initiative geared towards ensuring free, fair, credible and violence-free elections in Nigeria, particularly the southwest geopolitical zone. -Advertisement- The Executive Director of NIGAWD, Abimnola Aladejare-Salako who is also the convener of the Ekiti Youth Agenda campaign disclosed that the candidates of the All Progressives Congress(APC) Hon Biodun Abayomi Oyebanji (BAO), People’s Democratic Party(PDP) Hon Bisi Kolawole and the  Social Democratic Party (SDP), Engineer Segun Oni have keyed into the agenda and endorsed same ahead of the off-season election. The NIGWD Boss explained that the VNF campaign promotes constructive youth participation in Nigeria’s political and electoral processes by promoting peaceful and constructive youth engagement with stakeholders before, during, and after elections. “NIGAWD begins advocacy engagement with candidates in the 2022 off-cycle Governorship election in Ekiti State with the VOTE NOT FIGHT, ELECTION NO BE WAR Message and Commitment Ask for the scale-up of the implementation of Ekiti Youth Agenda Document being reviewed by Ekiti youth groups.” She added that an  advocacy visit was made to the office of the Governor and the Wife of the Governor, also to get  their commitments to the Vote Not Fight Campaign Recall that the  USAID and US Embassy officials had recently met with the VNF team in Ekiti where they sought greater partnership ahead of the poll. POLL On  the delegation was Political Officer, Janine Lewis; Regional Security Officer, James Suor; Political Specialist, Arnold Abulime; Democracy Officer, United States Agency for International Development (USAID) and Sterling Roop; Program Management Specialist, USAID, Halima Abubakar The interaction afforded NIGAWD to intimate the international development partners of the success stories of the VNF and its challenges. The meeting also dwelt on how to secure greater commitment to peace by the critical stakeholders and election gladiators.